name: COMMONWEALTH of Pennsylvania, Petitioner, v. Dorothy DENNIS, Respondent

parties: COMMONWEALTH of Pennsylvania, Petitioner, v. Dorothy DENNIS, Respondent.

opinions.text:
ORDER
PER CURIAM:
AND NOW, this 23rd day of April, 1996, the Petition for Allowance of Appeal is hereby granted with oral argument on whether the time differential between the administration of a breathalyzer test and commission of the offense of driving under the influence vitiates the effect of 75 Pa.C.S.A. § 1547(d)(1).
opinions.author: PER CURIAM:

casebody.head_matter:
674 A.2d 243
COMMONWEALTH of Pennsylvania, Petitioner, v. Dorothy DENNIS, Respondent.
Supreme Court of Pennsylvania.
April 23, 1996.
